column5: Buddy made the right call and was rewarded with this beast.  Took it about 10 mins after sunset, he knew it was coming (Heard it come through the swamp and into the hardwoods) but it was a race between the deer showing up first or darkness....   It's funny though, he told me if it was still light out that he probably wouldn't have taken the shot as he's seen deer quite a bit bigger then this on the property. Personally, if it's got spikes I'm taking it down   What a gorgeous animal, fattest deer I've ever seen as well.  This thing was an absolute piggy!  I'll be back at it next weekend, let's hope my luck turns!
That is a PIG good job buddy
I didn't shoot it, I just took the pic!
Nice buck, have one of similar size +/- in my yard with a 12 pt rack.
Holy chubby! You guys in farm country or the bush?  damn, these reports make me wish I didn't have to work.
Bigger than that? The censors would not let me exclaim my surprise.
Nice Buck. Is hunting after dark legal?
Nice buck!
You have 30 minutes after sunset Dax...
Nice Buck. Is hunting after dark legal?  Half hour before sunrise and a half hour after sunset is legal.  We took the pic well after it was shot.
oh christ that's big! Not sure I could keep my aim straight seeing that thing come towards me.  Good luck next weekend, I can't imagine a bigger one.

Wow! Now thats a stud!  My kiddos tried this weekend but no luck. They tracked a buck but lost it at dark. They were bummed but they got lotsa partridge and rabbits?  If you get a bigger buck then that I cant wait to see it!
Sweet buck!  He's gotta be on the juice that one.
Beauty Buck!  He must've been part of the Russian Olympic program.  Good luck next weekend.  Cheers, Mark
Beauty! No orange, no tag? LOL  S.
Beauty! No orange, no tag? LOL  S.  Orange vest was taken off for the pic, tag was put on after we snapped some pics.
Wow that is a huge Buck put the time in Bill and yours will come.

I had to wait to get home to see the picture. HOLLY CRAP  Look how thick that front quarter is. That could feed a family for a year alone.LOL  Congrats to your bud, bud.  Now for you to get yours.   Buddy must of really been sweating it out, as his camo makeup is all smeared on his face. LMAO
things so fat it wont even take a cut of pork to make sausage, nice meal you got there
That's a very nice Big Buck!!! Haha. Close to 200lbs?? There is quite a bit of meat there. Don't sweat it Bill, you'll get a nice one. Keep putting the time in.

That's a very nice Big Buck!!! Haha. Close to 200lbs?? There is quite a bit of meat there. Don't sweat it Bill, you'll get a nice one. Keep putting the time in.  My buddy guesses that deer went probably 220 or so.   I'm not too worried, I just need to put more time in the stand.  I'm still kicking myself for not taking that spot though! lol!
You know how it works bill! If you would have chosen that stand your buddy still probably woulda got it??
Awesome buck
east-european greasers probably got there ahead of you  :D

My buddy guesses that deer went probably 220 or so.   I'm not too worried, I just need to put more time in the stand.  I'm still kicking myself for not taking that spot though! lol!  yes , very nice buck, 220 and that would be field dressed looks about right.
